# Bark & Bite — CyberAv3ngers IOC Infrastructure Rules
# File: cyberav3ngers-ioc-aa26-097a.rules
# Version: 4.0.8 (MERGED into iranian-apt-detection.rules as of v4.0.10)
# Date: 2026-04-17
# Credit: Bark & Bite Security
# License: MIT
#
# DEPRECATED: These rules have been merged into iranian-apt-detection.rules (v4.0.10).
# This file is retained for backward compatibility but should no longer be loaded
# separately. Loading both this file AND iranian-apt-detection.rules will cause
# duplicate SID errors (2000496, 2000497).
#
# Original: IOC IP rules from CISA Advisory AA26-097A (April 7, 2026).
# Complements behavioral detection in iranian-apt-detection.rules (SIDs 2000478-2000485).
#
# Attribution: CyberAv3ngers (IRGC-CEC / Shahid Kaveh Group / Storm-0784 /
#   Bauxite / UNC5691 / Hydro Kitten)
# Context: Six-agency advisory confirming operational disruption at multiple
#   US critical infrastructure sites (WWS, Energy, Gov). Actors used Rockwell
#   Studio 5000 from a single multi-homed Windows engineering workstation
#   (185.82.73.x) to connect to internet-exposed CompactLogix/Micro850 PLCs
#   via EtherNet/IP port 44818. Deployed Dropbear SSH, extracted/modified ACD
#   project files, manipulated SCADA HMI displays.
#
# DEPLOY NOTE: Priority:1 ICS/OT rules. Enable on OT-adjacent segments.
#   If 185.82.73.0/24 is reassigned to legitimate hosting, disable SID 2000496.
#
# MITRE: T0883 (Internet Accessible Device), T0885 (Commonly Used Port),
#   T1219 (Remote Access Tools), T1565.001 (Stored Data Manipulation)
# Requires: Suricata 7.0+

# CyberAv3ngers Engineering Workstation — 7 IPs on 185.82.73.0/24
# DISABLED (2026-04-24): Rules merged into iranian-apt-detection.rules v4.0.10.
# These duplicates cause SID conflict errors when both files are loaded.
# See iranian-apt-detection.rules SID 2000496-2000497 for active versions.
#alert ip [185.82.73.162,185.82.73.164,185.82.73.165,185.82.73.167,185.82.73.168,185.82.73.170,185.82.73.171] any -> $HOME_NET any (msg:"Bark&Bite - Iranian CyberAv3ngers Engineering Workstation IOC AA26-097A 2026"; priority:1; threshold:type limit, track by_src, count 1, seconds 300; reference:url,cisa.gov/news-events/cybersecurity-advisories/aa26-097a; classtype:trojan-activity; sid:2000496; rev:1; metadata:policy max-detect-ips drop, created_at 2026_04_17, updated_at 2026_04_17;)

# CyberAv3ngers Staging Server — 135.136.1.133
# DISABLED (2026-04-24): See above.
#alert ip 135.136.1.133 any -> $HOME_NET any (msg:"Bark&Bite - Iranian CyberAv3ngers Staging Server IOC AA26-097A 2026"; priority:2; threshold:type limit, track by_src, count 1, seconds 300; reference:url,cisa.gov/news-events/cybersecurity-advisories/aa26-097a; classtype:trojan-activity; sid:2000497; rev:1; metadata:policy max-detect-ips drop, created_at 2026_04_17, updated_at 2026_04_17;)
